name: Cyanidin
description:
Cyanidin cation is an anthocyanidin cation that is flavylium substituted at positions 3, 3', 4', 5 and 7 by hydroxy groups. It has a role as a metabolite, a neuroprotective agent and an antioxidant. It is a conjugate acid of a cyanidin(1-).
Cyanidin is a natural product found in Salix candida, Eleocharis dulcis, and other organisms with data available.
